ARTICLE.TITLE: Liberman: 'No place for extraneous elections'
ARTICLE.TEXT:
Yisrael Beytenu chairman MK Avigdor Liberman spoke about the budget crisis and the chance that there may be new elections.

"I met this morning with President Reuven Rivlin, to discuss the urgent issues on Israel's agenda," Liberman tweeted. "We agreed that at this time, first and foremost, we need to deal with the serious economic crisis and pass a budget, and fight the coronavirus. During a time of crisis, there is no place for extraneous elections which stem only from personal considerations."
